full_affiliations: ["Mary Atkinson Smith, DNP, MSN, BSN, is a board certified nurse practitioner and registered nurse first assistant at Starkville Orthopedic Clinic, in addition to the cofounder of Starkville Orthopaedic Clinic located in a rural community of Mississippi. She has additional certifications as an orthopedic nurse practitioner and in perioperative nursing. Dr. Smith is also an assistant professor and assistant program director for South University College of Nursing and Public Health. She also serves as the Education and Program Director for the Mississippi Rural Health Association. William Todd Smith, MD, is a board certified orthopedic surgeon and is also a cofounder of Starkville Orthopaedic Clinic. Dr. Smith also has a subspecialty certification in sports medicine. He completed an orthopedic surgery residency at the University of Mississippi Medical Center in Jackson, MS. Dr. Smith provides orthopedic care to the rural community of Starkville, MS, and residents in the surrounding counties. Marietta Stanton, PhD, MSN, BSN, is a board certified nurse practitioner and a certified case manager. She is currently a professor of nursing at the Capstone College of Nursing in Tuscaloosa, AL. Dr. Stanton has served on active duty as the Senior Case Manager for Clinical Operations, Southeast Regional Medical Command. She has also played an instrumental role in developing the Capstone College of Nursing's Masters' Program in Case Management and Leadership for rural populations."]
